          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-05-11 21:47:33" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>any instrument or means of binding or tying; used for binding objects together or restraining prisoners</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>bonds</Gloss>
                <Gloss>chains</Gloss>
                <Gloss>fetters</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In translating {S:04401602600042} one may often use a descriptive phrase, for example, ‘those things that bound them’ or ‘things with which they were tied.’ It is generally more satisfactory, however, to employ wherever possible a more specific referent, for example, ‘ropes,’ ‘chains’ or ‘fetters.’</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
